msContents.summary: Critical portrait of individuals in the court of Saxony under Elector Frederick Augustus I, also known as August der Starke, who became King Augustus II of Poland.

msItem.title: Le portrait de la cour de Saxe
msItem.author: Wolfframsdorff, Johann Friedrich von, ca. 1674-1712

supportDesc.extent: 92 leaves : 320 x 199 (225 x 101) mm. bound to 329 x 205 mm

collation.p: Paper; 92; 1-11⁸, 12⁶; [i], 1-54, 56-76, 78-93; contemporary foliation in ink, upper right recto. Signatures A through M (omitting I), lower center recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in a single column of 26-33 lines on the inner half of each page, with the pages having been folded to establish the outer margin.

origin.p: Written in Saxony in the early 18th century (Zacour-Hirsch).
